results.name: Column 2 of A277898; position of the second occurrence of n in A277892.
comment: a(n) = the second smallest number k for which A277892(k) = n, where A277892(n) = the number of prime divisors (counted with multiplicity) of A048675(n).
Note that the sequence is not monotonic: a(22) = 6241 and a(23) = 5378.
example: A277892[2..4] = [0, 1, 1], thus as the second 1 occurs at A277892(4), a(1) = 4.
program: (define (A277900 n) (A277898bi n 2)) ;; Code for A277898bi given in A277898.
